## Issue

When session creation fails, the error is caught and logged to console only. The UI stays at the confirm step with the button re-enabled. No error message is shown to the user.

```typescript
} catch (err) {
    console.error('Failed to create session:', err);
    // No user-visible feedback
} finally {
    submitting = false;
}
```

Also: because test_id is sent instead of test_ids (a separate P1 bug), if the backend ever adds extra='forbid' validation, this catch block will be the only thing the user sees — an empty confirm step with no explanation.

## Fix
Add an error state variable and display it:
```typescript
let submitError: string | null = null;

// In catch:
submitError = 'Erro ao criar sessão. Tente novamente.';

// In template (confirm step):
{#if submitError}
  <p class='text-sm text-red-600'>{submitError}</p>
{/if}
```

## Severity
P2 — users have no feedback on failure; will retry blindly or abandon.

## Location
- cognitest/frontend/src/lib/components/OrderTestModal.svelte:89-91

## Validation Criteria
- [ ] Session creation failure shows an error message in the modal
- [ ] Error message clears when user retries
- [ ] submitting button re-enables after failure

## Issue

After OrderTestModal successfully creates a session and closes, the Recent Sessions card (Card 2) still shows the old list. There is no loadDashboard() call or state refresh triggered on modal close. The user must manually reload the page to see the new session.

```svelte
<OrderTestModal
    {testDefs}
    on:close={() => (showOrderModal = false)}
/>
```

The close handler only hides the modal, never refreshes data.

## Fix
Track whether a session was created in the modal, and refresh on close:
```svelte
on:close={(e) => {
    showOrderModal = false;
    if (e.detail?.sessionCreated) loadDashboard();
}}
```
The modal should dispatch close with { sessionCreated: true } on the success step.

## Severity
P3 — UX issue; data is stale but not wrong.

## Location
- cognitest/frontend/src/routes/(app)/dashboard/+page.svelte (modal close handler)
- cognitest/frontend/src/lib/components/OrderTestModal.svelte (dispatch event)

## Issue

`loadDashboard()` unconditionally sets `loading = true`, which replaces the entire card grid with a full-page spinner. This is called after the `OrderTestModal` closes on success:

```svelte
on:close={(e) => {
    showOrderModal = false;
    if (e.detail?.sessionCreated) loadDashboard();  // triggers full-page spinner
}}
```

The user just completed a session creation — the success screen disappears, and they stare at a full spinner for the duration of 3 parallel API calls. The `Order Test` CTA button is hidden during loading.

Also: there is no guard against concurrent `loadDashboard()` calls. If called from both `onMount` and the close handler simultaneously, whichever finishes last wins — last-writer-wins race on `revenue`, `sessions`, `testDefs`.

## Severity
P1 — Jarring UX regression immediately after the user's primary action. The success state is destroyed before the user can process it.

## Location
- `cognitest/frontend/src/routes/(app)/dashboard/+page.svelte:66` (loading = true)
- `cognitest/frontend/src/routes/(app)/dashboard/+page.svelte:122-126` (close handler)

## Fix Option A (recommended)
Use a generation counter to guard concurrent calls AND a separate `reloading` flag for post-creation reloads that shows a subtle spinner only inside the sessions card:
```typescript
let loadGen = 0;
async function loadDashboard(showFullSpinner = true) {
    const gen = ++loadGen;
    if (showFullSpinner) loading = true;
    // ...fetch...
    if (gen !== loadGen) return;
    loading = false;
}
// In close handler:
if (e.detail?.sessionCreated) loadDashboard(false);
```

## Fix Option B
After session creation, prepend the new session directly to `sessions` from the data already returned by `handleConfirm` — skip the full reload.

## Validation Criteria
- [ ] After closing OrderTestModal with success, the dashboard cards remain visible (no full-page spinner)
- [ ] Sessions card updates to show the new session
- [ ] Two rapid loadDashboard calls don't produce stale state

## Issue

The debounced patient search in OrderTestModal.svelte has no out-of-order response guard. If the user types quickly, request A (for 'Ma') and request B (for 'Mar') both fire. If B resolves first and A resolves late, searchResults is overwritten with stale results from A — showing 'Ma' results while the input shows 'Mar'.

In a clinical platform, this can cause a clinician to select the wrong patient silently.

```typescript
// Current — no serial guard
searchTimeout = setTimeout(async () => {
    searching = true;
    searchResults = await searchPatients(searchQuery);  // can resolve out of order
    searching = false;
}, 300);
```

## Fix
Add a serial number counter:
```typescript
let searchSerial = 0;

searchTimeout = setTimeout(async () => {
    const serial = ++searchSerial;
    searching = true;
    const results = await searchPatients(searchQuery);
    if (serial !== searchSerial) return; // superseded by newer request
    searchResults = results;
    searching = false;
}, 300);
```

Also: searchTimeout and copyLink timeout are not cleared on component destroy — add onDestroy cleanup.

## Severity
P1 — can cause wrong patient selection with no visible error. Clinical safety issue.

## Location
- cognitest/frontend/src/lib/components/OrderTestModal.svelte:37-48

## Validation Criteria
- [ ] Typing quickly shows only results for the final query, never stale earlier results
- [ ] searchTimeout cleared in onDestroy
- [ ] copyLink setTimeout ID stored and cleared in onDestroy

Create reusable PhoneInput component for MedSimples frontend with country code selector.

## What

Build a Material UI phone input component that combines country code selector with phone number input, following existing MedSimples patterns.

## Context

- From research: Recommended libraries are react-international-phone, mui-phone-input, or react-phone-input-2
- From codebase analysis: PatientForm uses simple TextField with generic handleChange
- Must follow MUI conventions: fullWidth, labelId on Select, error/helperText for validation
- Store country code and phone separately in state (not combined)
- Organization default_tel_country_code used as default
- From research: Apply formatting on display, NOT storage

## Component Props

```typescript
interface PhoneInputProps {
  value: string;                    // Phone number without country code
  countryCode: string;              // E.g., '55', '1'
  onChange: (phone: string, countryCode: string) => void;
  defaultCountryCode?: string;      // From org.default_tel_country_code
  label: string;                    // E.g., "WhatsApp", "Telefone 1"
  error?: string;                   // Validation error message
  disabled?: boolean;
  required?: boolean;
}
```

## Features

1. **Country Selector:**
   - MUI Select or Autocomplete with country dial codes
   - Display: flag emoji (optional) + dial code + country name
   - Common countries at top: Brazil (55), USA (1), Portugal (351)
   - Full country list below (alphabetical)
   - Default to organization's `default_tel_country_code`

2. **Phone Input:**
   - MUI TextField for phone number
   - Auto-format display based on selected country (using libphonenumber-js)
   - Strip formatting before calling onChange (store digits only)

3. **Validation:**
   - Use `libphonenumber-js` to validate phone based on country
   - Show error via helperText prop
   - Validate on blur (not on every keystroke)

4. **Layout:**
   - Country selector (150px width) + Phone input (flex grow)
   - Wrap both in Box with display flex
   - Follow MUI spacing conventions from codebase

## Implementation

**File:** `frontend/src/components/PhoneInput.tsx`

**Dependencies to add:**
```bash
cd medsimples/frontend
bun add libphonenumber-js
```

**Code Pattern:**
```typescript
import { TextField, Select, MenuItem, FormControl, Box } from '@mui/material';
import { parsePhoneNumber } from 'libphonenumber-js';

export const PhoneInput: React.FC<PhoneInputProps> = ({ ... }) => {
  const [displayValue, setDisplayValue] = useState('');
  const [validationError, setValidationError] = useState('');

  // Format display, store raw
  const handlePhoneChange = (e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {
    const raw = e.target.value.replace(/\D/g, ''); // Digits only for storage
    setDisplayValue(formatPhoneForDisplay(raw, countryCode)); // Format for display
    onChange(raw, countryCode); // Pass raw to parent
  };

  // Validate on blur
  const handleBlur = () => {
    try {
      const parsed = parsePhoneNumber(value, countryCode as CountryCode);
      if (!parsed?.isValid()) {
        setValidationError('Número de telefone inválido');
      } else {
        setValidationError('');
      }
    } catch {
      setValidationError('Número de telefone inválido');
    }
  };

  return (
    <Box display="flex" gap={1}>
      <FormControl sx={{ minWidth: 150 }}>
        <Select
          value={countryCode}
          onChange={(e) => onChange(value, e.target.value)}
          disabled={disabled}
        >
          {/* Brazil, US, Portugal at top */}
          <MenuItem value="55">🇧🇷 +55 Brasil</MenuItem>
          <MenuItem value="1">🇺🇸 +1 USA</MenuItem>
          <MenuItem value="351">🇵🇹 +351 Portugal</MenuItem>
          {/* Full list below */}
        </Select>
      </FormControl>
      <TextField
        fullWidth
        label={label}
        value={displayValue}
        onChange={handlePhoneChange}
        onBlur={handleBlur}
        error={!!error || !!validationError}
        helperText={error || validationError}
        disabled={disabled}
        required={required}
      />
    </Box>
  );
};
```

## Testing

- [ ] Component renders with country selector and phone input
- [ ] Defaults to organization's default_tel_country_code
- [ ] onChange provides both phone (digits only) and country code separately
- [ ] Validation works for Brazil (+55): 10-11 digits
- [ ] Validation works for US (+1): 10 digits
- [ ] Error message shown in Portuguese via helperText
- [ ] Country selector includes Brazil, US, Portugal at top
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works (tab between selector and input)
- [ ] Screen reader announces label and error (accessibility)
- [ ] Disabled state prevents interaction
- [ ] Required attribute adds asterisk to label

## Validation

- [ ] Component file exists at frontend/src/components/PhoneInput.tsx
- [ ] libphonenumber-js installed in package.json
- [ ] Component exports PhoneInputProps interface
- [ ] Follows MUI patterns: fullWidth, error/helperText
- [ ] Stores phone digits only (no formatting in value prop)
- [ ] Validates on blur, not on every keystroke
- [ ] Returns both phone and countryCode via single onChange callback
- [ ] Accessible (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation)

## Dependencies

Blocks: medsimples-152 (needs Organization.default_tel_country_code)

