## Issue
login/+page.svelte has password = ''; loading = false; repeated in 4 error branches and a catch block. handleKeyDown is a 3-line Enter handler that duplicates native form submission behavior.

## Severity
P3 NICE-TO-HAVE — 18 LOC removed with no behavior change.

## Fix
1. Use try/finally for cleanup:
```typescript
async function handleSubmit(): Promise<void> {
    if (\!email.trim() || \!password) { error = 'Preencha e-mail e senha.'; return; }
    error = null;
    loading = true;
    try {
        // ... all branching logic, remove password='' and loading=false from each branch
        await goto('/commissions');
    } catch {
        error = 'Erro de conexão. Tente novamente.';
        password = '';
    } finally {
        loading = false;
    }
}
```
2. Remove handleKeyDown function entirely
3. Remove on:keydown handler from the form div
4. Remove the svelte-ignore a11y-no-noninteractive-element-interactions comment (was masking this misplaced handler)

## Validation Criteria
- [ ] loading = false; only appears in finally block
- [ ] handleKeyDown removed
- [ ] Form still submits on Enter (native behavior)

## Issue
The catch block in /(app)/+layout.ts uses a fragile duck-type check to re-throw SvelteKit redirect objects:
```typescript
if (e instanceof Response || (e as { status?: number })?.status) throw e;
```
SvelteKit's redirect() does NOT throw a Response — it throws a Redirect object. The instanceof Response check is always false. The code works only accidentally via the duck-typed .status check. This will also accidentally re-throw any error object that has a numeric status property.

## Severity
P2 IMPORTANT — Currently functional by accident; breaks under edge cases and misleads maintainers.

## Location
cognitest/frontend/src/routes/(app)/+layout.ts lines 19-22

## Fix
```typescript
import { redirect, isRedirect } from '@sveltejs/kit';
// ...
} catch (e) {
    if (isRedirect(e)) throw e;
    // Network error — let it through
}
```

## Validation Criteria
