## What
Remove derived state computation inside useEffect in VisitList.tsx:227. Compute during render instead.

## Context
Derived state inside useEffect creates a one-render lag (state is stale for one frame), adds unnecessary re-renders, and is an established React anti-pattern. The fix is to compute the derived value directly during render using useMemo or a plain const.

Example of the pattern to remove:
```typescript
// BAD — useEffect just to compute derived state
useEffect(() => {
  setDerived(computeFrom(dep1, dep2));
}, [dep1, dep2]);
```

Example of the fix:
```typescript
// GOOD — compute during render
const derived = useMemo(() => computeFrom(dep1, dep2), [dep1, dep2]);
// or just: const derived = computeFrom(dep1, dep2);
```

