## Why This Matters
A POST to /api/visits/123/medications should invalidate /api/visits caches, but the current regex only strips the trailing ID, not the full sub-resource path.

## Fix
Extract the first two path segments as the base:
```typescript
export function invalidateCachePrefix(url: string) {
  // Extract base resource path (e.g., /api/visits from /api/visits/123/medications)
  const parts = url.split('/').filter(Boolean);
  const basePath = '/' + parts.slice(0, 2).join('/');
  for (const key of requestCache.keys()) {
    if (key.startsWith(basePath)) {
      requestCache.delete(key);
    }
  }
}
```

